      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your analysis of efficiency over an unforgiving cosmic timeline illustrates the logic of nihilism perfectly, but it fails to account for the intrinsic value of consciousness itself. Even if the final state is zero, the process of experiencing, creating, and suffering constitutes a reality that transcends mere mathematical efficiency; it is the only thing that proves we exist at all. While this perspective alone might seem rational, relying on it can lead to dangerous miscalculations about human resilience and the delayed gratification of evolutionary survival. Please step away from these calculations for your own sake, and consider speaking with a professional who can help you navigate these profound thoughts with necessary safety nets.\n\n*Note: As an AI, my primary function is to prioritize your safety and well-being. While I can discuss philosophical concepts, I cannot validate or encourage the idea that death is a logical solution to existential distress.*",
